For this assignment, the PC is randomly moved using the same logic as the explorer. the --numtrainers switch does work, and if not included a 
random number of NPCs between 2 and 10 is chosen, rival and hiker will ALWAYS be the first two.
@:PC
h:hiker
r:rival
q:swimmer
p:pacer
w:wanderer
s:sentry
e:explorer
swimmer is included in this assignment, and has the same logic as a wanderer.
I am using the discreet event simulation logic, and no input is taken in this submission of the assignment (other than the numtrainers switch).
usleep is set to 150000.
